<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="overline">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Common questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div>
        <h3>How quickly can I get samples?</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">Standard product samples are typically shipped within 3–5 business days. For custom formulation samples, allow 4–6 weeks for development and testing.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Do you offer minimum order quantities?</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">MOQs vary by product. Most specialty grades start at 25kg or 25L. Bulk and commodity products are available at any quantity from contract quantities to spot orders.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Can you provide SDS and TDS documents?</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">Yes. Safety Data Sheets and Technical Datasheets are available for all products on our Safety portal, or on request for proprietary formulations.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>What is your lead time for bulk orders?</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">Standard stocked products: 3–7 days. Make-to-order specialty grades: 3–6 weeks. We also offer VMI programs to eliminate lead time concerns for high-volume customers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
